cs.NI, cs.MM, cs.SI, cs.IT, cs.CR 

Reasoning: 
- cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) is the most likely category as the paper focuses on QoE of video streaming in wireless networks and proposes an analytical framework to compute the closed-form starvation probability based on ordinary differential equations. 
- cs.MM (Multimedia) is also likely as the paper deals with video streaming and user behavior. 
- cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) is a possible category as the paper collects view records from a large streaming provider and performs an in-depth measurement study on flow arrival and viewing time. 
- cs.IT (Information Theory) is another possible category as the paper proposes an online Bayesian approach to infer the viewing time of each incoming flow with the "least" information from content providers. 
- cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) is a less likely category as there is no mention of security or cryptography in the paper.
